China, U.S. Agree on Technical Details Concerning Return of EP-3 Plane
China and the United States has reached an agreement on the technical
details concerning the return of the U.S. EP-3 reconnaissance plane,
Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi announced Thursday afternoon at a
regular press conference.
Sun said the two sides are making preparations and arrangements for the
disassembling and shipping of the plane, and the U.S. side will hire a
cargo plane to carry the disassembled plane back home.
The agreement was reached Wednesday.
